73 // Very useful tool for identifying a single bad function compilation.
74 // Use with a tool like `find-first-fail`: https://gitlab.com/ole.tange/tangetools/-/blob/master/find-first-fail/find-first-fail
75 // 1. Enable ENABLE_BISECT_TOOL below.
76 // 2. Make a new script `tmp.sh` calling a failing replay (change to use the failing replay, but don't change --extra_args):
77 // python tests/run_replay_tests.py --filter stellar --frame 40000 --not_interactive --extra_args="-replay-fail-assert-instant -jit-precompile -jit-threads 0 -test-jit-bisect $1"
78 // 3. Run the bisect script (may need to increase the end range if script is large, as it is based on number of functions):
79 // bash ~/tools/find-first-fail.sh -s 0 -e 10000 -v -q bash tmp.sh
80 // 4. For the number given, set `-test-jit-bisect` to that, and set a breakpoint
81 // where specified in bisect_tool_should_skip. Whatever function being processed is the one to focus on.
82 // #define ENABLE_BISECT_TOOL
83 246163 static bool bisect_tool_should_skip()
84 {
85 #ifdef ENABLE_BISECT_TOOL
86 static int64_t c = 0;
87 static int64_t x = get_flag_int("-test-jit-bisect").value();
88 // Skip the first x calls.
89 bool skip = 0 <= c && c < x;
90 c++;
91 if (!skip)
92 // Set a breakpoint here.
93 x = x;
94 return skip;
95 #else
96 246163 return false;
97 #endif
98 }
